      "content": "hey i'm working on a paper for my linguistics class and i'm stuck on this part. i have these two short paragraphs from different student essays. i need to analyze which one would be viewed as more \"intellectually competent\" or \"academically professional\" in a high-level university seminar setting. \n\nText A: \"The socioeconomic implications of urbanization are multifaceted, often leading to significant shifts in demographic distribution and resource allocation across metropolitan sectors.\"\n\nText B: \"When cities get big, it really changes how folks live and where they end up, and it makes it hard to get everything where it needs to go in different parts of town.\"\n\nwhich one sounds more like a serious academic writer to you?",
